CHANGES: 12 July 2005

### Mike Kay changes:
### Carmelo changes:

http://www.w3.org/Member/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=119

Test rdb-queries-results-q9 (from use case R) uses the obsolete function names
get-month-from-date() and get-year-from-date(). The "get-" prefix has been removed.

##

http://www.w3.org/Member/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=121

Use case q5 (named as xmp-queries-results-q5) copies a text node from the source
document to the result document using the construct

<price-bstore2>{ $a/price/text() }</price-bstore2>

The relevant element in the source document is

<price> 65.95</price>

but in the reference results it appears as

<price>65.95</price>

Removing the leading space would be legitimate in a schema-aware query that
validates the price element as a decimal; but there is no schema in this
example, so the value is untypedAtomic, and the leading space should therefore
be present in the result (or absent from the source!)

## I removed the space from the source.

http://www.w3.org/Member/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=124

Use case NS q5 copies a <record> element from the source document to the result
document. There are two <remark> elements in this <record>, one English and one
German: the text of both remarks contain significant trailing whitespace in the
source document which is wrongly omitted from the expected results.

## Removed trailing whitespace from source.

http://www.w3.org/Member/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=148

Use case STRING results for q1 and q2 are incorrect: the expected results omit
whitespace that is present in the source document.

Q1:

Disagree - this looks correct. Source is indented.

<title>Foobar Corporation releases its new line of Foo
products today</title>
   <title>Foobar Corporation releases its new line of Foo products
   today</title>
<title>Foobar Corporation is suing Gorilla Corporation for patent
infringement </title> 
   <title>Foobar Corporation is suing Gorilla Corporation for
   patent infringement </title>

Q2:

<news_item>
    <title> Gorilla Corporation acquires YouNameItWeIntegrateIt.com </title>
    <date>1-20-2000</date>
</news_item>
<news_item>
    <title>Foobar Corporation releases its new line of Foo products today</title>
    <date>1-20-2000</date>
</news_item>
<news_item>
    <title>Foobar Corporation is suing Gorilla Corporation for patent
    infringement </title>
    <date>1-20-2000</date>
</news_item>

Results for q4 and q5 are OK after normalize-space() is applied - but that isn't
supposed to be allowed.

### Changed get-XXX-() date functions to current names in Q9.

